The paper proposes a method for learning binary codes for large-scale information retrieval, which involves optimizing multivariate performance measures such as AUC and NDCG. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on learning binary codes for information retrieval and image retrieval tasks, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
